00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,720
{\an8}You need to take the kids to Khanin.

2
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,720
{\an8}He'll take you all to a hiding place.

3
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,560
{\an8}- Mom!
- No!

4
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:46,520
{\an8}Dad!

5
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,280
{\an8}Dad, look out!

6
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:53,240
{\an8}If you want Fire Phoenix
to help you, it'll cost you.

7
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:55,800
{\an8}They can take my life.

8
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:59,120
{\an8}We'll hunt them down together.
Even if they hide in the shadows,

9
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,000
{\an8}Fire Phoenix needs to be exposed!

10
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,840
Naruban

11
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:38,680
is the keyman who's under
Fire Phoenix's protection.

12
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:43,040
He's a businessman
who'll change the world for the better.

13
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:47,960
Equality and justice

14
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:51,120
will come.

15
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:36,400
Tell Mom I miss her, Dad.

16
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:43,160
I offered alms
for your wedding anniversary this morning.

17
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:58,360
Hello!

18
00:04:58,440 --> 00:05:02,600
Hi! It's me again,
your favorite seller, Aru!

19
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:06,560
<i>Today I've got Korean-style outfits</i>
<i>for you all.</i>

20
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:10,360
Hurry before someone preorders them.
Whoa, five viewers now! Okay!

21
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,360
<i>Mr. Handsome.</i>

22
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:14,760
<i>You can buy it for your girlfriend,</i>

23
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:17,040
<i>or even your mother.</i>

24
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,680
Saranghaeyo.

25
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:23,040
<i>Does anybody want this dress?</i>

26
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:25,480
<i>It's so pretty, and form-fitting too.</i>

27
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:29,920
Okay, looks like no one wants it yet.

28
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:34,400
I have to take a break now.
All that selling got me hungry.

29
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:48,960
Watch out for the street cameras.

30
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:15,320
Where's the designer
you wanted to proudly present?

31
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,360
He turned off his phone.

32
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:40,000
- Someone's inside.
- How's that possible?

33
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:43,000
Last time I went there,
it's an abandoned house.

34
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:27,560
Someone wants what's inside the house too.

35
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:32,000
The intel Inspector Phumin had

36
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:36,960
contains evidence on who's involved
with Fire Phoenix.

37
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:40,360
Maybe Fire Phoenix
already sent someone there before you.

38
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,760
I didn't see their face, though.

39
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,880
You don't have to go there anymore.
I'll keep watch.

40
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:52,640
You'd do better at 3C, where you can go
in and out without suspicion.

41
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:08,120
Please thank Pat for me, Sun.

42
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:12,240
She helped pay off Scene's medical fees
and your dad's gambling debt.

43
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:16,120
We never could've paid it all off
in our lifetime.

44
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:21,400
I'll get going then, Mom.

45
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:23,360
If you need anything, call me.

46
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:26,120
I'll be going now, okay?

47
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:31,960
Bye.

48
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,800
Two hot chocolates, please.

49
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:46,080
{\an8}<i>If you aren't ready to be my present,</i>

50
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:49,280
{\an8}<i>we can stay in the past for now.</i>

51
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,400
{\an8}ARU

52
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:53,400
{\an8}<i>I'll always love you and understand you.</i>

53
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:09,840
How'd it go with your mom and sister?

54
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:12,800
Pretty good.

55
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:15,520
My mom said she really appreciated
what you did.

56
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:19,680
I'm just glad to see you happy.

57
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,200
Sure.

58
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,560
Won't you read that text?

59
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:35,000
{\an8}ARU

60
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,600
Shameless bitch!

61
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:37,880
Pat, don't!

62
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,600
- Sun!
- <i>Who are you?</i>

63
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,920
Why'd you text my boyfriend?
Do you wanna die?

64
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,480
Let me warn you again,

65
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:53,280
if you don't want any trouble,

66
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:55,840
<i>stop pestering me and my girlfriend,</i>

67
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:57,280
or I'll call the cops.

68
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:00,360
Sun--

69
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,000
I blocked her.

70
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,360
Pat,

71
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,920
there's really nothing
going on between us.

72
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:17,200
Please, don't worry.

73
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:22,120
Pat.

74
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:24,200
I promise you're my only one.

75
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,440
Don't be mad. I'm sorry.

76
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,000
Please.

77
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:34,480
I have a cute boyfriend.
Of course I'd be jealous.

78
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:37,720
You're the sweetest.

79
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:55,880
Hot chocolate helps with sadness.

80
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:16,600
Thank you, Rin.

81
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:21,440
Thank you for being a true friend
when I'm at my worst.

82
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,080
There's a light in all of us.

83
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,280
That's what a friend of mine used to say.

84
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:38,280
The best friend of my life.

85
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:27,240
Rin, Rin!

86
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:28,840
Rin, where are you going?

87
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,760
Mr. Taiga's not here yet either.

88
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:34,680
Why aren't you here yet?

89
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:56,440
Hello.

90
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:59,960
I'm outside now. Looks like
someone got inside the house.

91
00:14:00,880 --> 00:14:02,680
Okay, I'll call you back.

92
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:18,080
Sorry, I was busy with drawing yesterday,

93
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:19,680
so I didn't turn on my phone.

94
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:21,320
It's alright.

95
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:24,880
Ms. Nun's in a meeting.
She'll be back in a moment.

96
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:36,960
Ms. Atinuch,

97
00:16:37,880 --> 00:16:41,320
is the aggressive security guard
not here today?

98
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:45,560
You mean Rin? She's so irresponsible.

99
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:47,600
Yesterday she took half a day off,

100
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:51,120
and today she called in sick
early in the morning.

101
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:53,920
But oh well, she did something great
that impressed the CEO,

102
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,040
so he promoted her so soon.

103
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:58,280
Do you happen to have her address?

104
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:01,480
Why would you need
a security guard's address?

105
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:05,440
I'd like to send her flowers.

106
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:07,760
But she's just security.

107
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:11,040
She saved me from the fire
in this building.

108
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:14,960
A bouquet of flowers
is just a small gesture.

109
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:18,880
Your heart's warmer
than any microwave, Mr. Taiga.

110
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:23,000
If I ever get sick, you can come
take care of me at my bedside.

111
00:17:25,839 --> 00:17:26,839
Here you go.

112
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:29,640
Thank you.

113
00:18:08,840 --> 00:18:10,240
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

114
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:12,360
I'm here to see
my girlfriend in that room.

115
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:16,240
I thought no one lived there.

116
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,360
Must be that girl I rarely see.

117
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:23,360
I think she's moved out.

118
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:25,760
You're her boyfriend.
Don't you know anything?

119
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:29,240
Excuse me.

120
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:51,960
<i>Sorry, the number you've dialed</i>
<i>is currently unavailable--</i>

121
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:01,280
<i>Sorry, the number you've dialed</i>
<i>is currently unavailable--</i>

122
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:08,320
If you're trying to track a woman,

123
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:13,840
there are better ways
than constantly calling her.

124
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,160
Rin's very careful.

125
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:21,360
You think she's with Fire Phoenix?

126
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:40,680
She's been keeping me away from Naruban,

127
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:43,360
and no one really knows her.

128
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,120
She acts like a shadow.

129
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:53,360
But you know a way to hunt shadows.

130
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:10,040
Dad, Nun's really crazy
about that mixed designer guy.

131
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:12,760
Who knows if she wants him
for work or for love.

132
00:20:12,840 --> 00:20:14,160
Your sister's here to work.

133
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:17,080
Instead of badmouthing people,

134
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:19,480
why don't you find something better to do?

135
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:24,320
If I did her job, it wouldn't
have turned out so crappy.

136
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:26,920
Get some real work done,

137
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,600
and don't you cause trouble
and drain my money again.

138
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:33,000
Don't think I won't disown you
just because I love your mom!

139
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:45,360
Thank you so much
for your work today, Mr. Taiga.

140
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:48,120
My pleasure.

141
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:02,760
I don't think
I've welcomed you officially,

142
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:04,520
Mr. Taiga.

143
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,040
Techut,

144
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:12,640
he's my guest. Mind your own business.

145
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:15,800
That means he's
Cosmic Central's guest too, no?

146
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:20,440
As an executive,
I've got to take care of him too.

147
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,600
Mr. Taiga's team is leaving now.

148
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:50,040
Mr. Techut, please don't.

149
00:21:58,640 --> 00:21:59,960
I didn't even do anything.

150
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,640
I'm just trying to greet her.

151
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:06,200
Techut.

152
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:11,640
We hired them to work for us, didn't we?

153
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:15,760
As the employer, I can talk to them.
Does anyone have a problem?

154
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:26,600
Call security!

155
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:31,120
Hey. Come with me!

156
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,280
Yes, you. Don't ask. Quick, follow me!

157
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:38,120
Come on, hurry!

158
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:40,800
Let go of me!

159
00:22:50,880 --> 00:22:53,360
Techut, get out now!

160
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:14,480
Follow him.

161
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:16,080
Don't let him get on this floor again.

162
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:34,200
Give me the usual, quick!

163
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:35,200
‪Yes, sir.

164
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:18,840
Ms. Ratee.

165
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:23,880
How come you're serving coffee here?

166
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:37,440
Of course, I have to take care
of our VIP guest who owns the building.

167
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:41,280
I own this café.

168
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:43,080
I just bought it, actually.

169
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:05,200
Is the coffee good?

170
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:08,120
Yes.

171
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:52,680
Stop moving. You'll bruise your cheek.

172
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:13,680
It'll hurt more if you move.

173
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:17,440
Can you just stay still for a minute?

174
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:37,320
Does your arm hurt?

175
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:39,520
What happened?

176
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:45,200
I fell down the stairs.

177
00:26:46,680 --> 00:26:47,600
Did you see a doctor?

178
00:26:49,280 --> 00:26:50,440
Want me to take you?

179
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:53,560
Stay away from me.

180
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:19,360
Here. Your severance pay.

181
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:23,560
I warned you not to get
in the way of our bosses.

182
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:27,320
You're firing me?

183
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:31,880
But I did nothing wrong.
I even got slapped.

184
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:36,200
Listen, forget telling the police,
the Ministry of Labor,

185
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:38,400
or social media.

186
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:42,240
Take the money and find a new job.

187
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:44,720
You can have a beef with anyone,

188
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:47,520
but not Cosmic Central Group.

189
00:27:52,520 --> 00:27:53,440
Take it.

190
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:21,880
I've taken care of it.

191
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:24,720
Now that she's got the money,
she'll probably go without a fuss.

192
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:40,920
This is the type of justice
good, dedicated people get.

193
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:49,160
I understand how painful it feels.

194
00:28:57,840 --> 00:28:58,960
Come on, hurry!

195
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:05,520
Just tell me who you work for.

196
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:09,800
If you don't want to say it,
point at his name.

197
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:14,760
He talked, sir.

198
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,200
We know who the leader is now.

199
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:19,520
Who said you can get involved
in this case, Punlop?

200
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:23,120
I just followed the clues.

201
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:25,080
We've been investigating this case
for years!

202
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:28,840
- This is not your duty!
- But I think it is.

203
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:31,160
I've been tracking
those human traffickers.

204
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:33,040
I'm sorry, sir.

205
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:37,600
I just don't want Thailand
to be a channel for human trafficking.

206
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:39,160
They treat people worse than animals.

207
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:41,960
They beat them, rape them, and kill them.

208
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:43,680
They don't have any mercy.

209
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:45,800
If we call our country
"The Land of Buddhism"

210
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:47,880
while we turn a blind eye
on those monsters

211
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:49,800
and let them exploit people for a living,

212
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:53,760
then we're no different
than those monsters.

213
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:08,480
All my dedication

214
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,640
really backfired.

215
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:17,200
I was under investigation for embezzlement

216
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:19,280
and was about to be fired.

217
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:23,760
Then the bosses at Fire Phoenix

218
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:27,160
lent a hand and proved my innocence

219
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,240
so I could go back to work.

220
00:30:37,080 --> 00:30:38,360
Justice…

221
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:41,320
does exist.

222
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,400
When you submit to no one,

223
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:47,640
you can't be a good cop

224
00:30:49,560 --> 00:30:51,120
just for praise or for when

225
00:30:52,120 --> 00:30:53,600
the Thai flag covers your coffin.

226
00:30:56,880 --> 00:30:59,560
A cop who can sacrifice
even their own life

227
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:03,480
must live with honor,

228
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:06,520
with people appreciating them.

229
00:31:31,240 --> 00:31:33,560
Rest assured, Mr. Taiga.

230
00:31:33,640 --> 00:31:36,280
Rin will no longer be around to bug you.

231
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:43,080
Please give me a moment.

232
00:32:05,520 --> 00:32:07,560
I need your help. Now.

233
00:32:12,200 --> 00:32:15,080
<i>What are you taking pictures for?</i>
<i>What the hell?!</i>

234
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:27,840
<i>What are you taking pictures for?</i>
<i>What the hell?!</i>

235
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:30,560
<i>All reporters outside,</i>
<i>please stop taking pictures.</i>

236
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,960
<i>Please give my client some privacy.</i>

237
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:41,560
How'd that page get that old video?
You said every video was deleted!

238
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:45,080
Your firm gets ten million
from my dad every year!

239
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:47,320
Why'd you do such a shitty job?

240
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:49,920
Find them and sue them all!

241
00:33:15,840 --> 00:33:17,400
What are you doing?

242
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:19,920
Can I help?

243
00:33:30,920 --> 00:33:32,240
I like this one.

244
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:36,960
Ms. Nun!

245
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:39,320
Ms. Nun,

246
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:40,960
look.

247
00:33:42,480 --> 00:33:44,800
Go check if my dad's seen it.

248
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:48,640
He probably did. Everyone's sharing it.

249
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:53,400
Here we go.

250
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:57,280
I'm getting so many notifications.
Must be all of my group chats.

251
00:33:59,400 --> 00:34:01,440
Is something wrong?

252
00:34:01,520 --> 00:34:02,760
It's nothing.

253
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:11,639
Please don't read the news.

254
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:20,480
"Shocking video, billionaire's son
goes berserk at police station,

255
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:25,159
tortures women,
treating them worse than dogs."

256
00:34:45,760 --> 00:34:48,719
Don't post anything.
Don't give any interviews.

257
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:51,600
Just stay as still as you can.

258
00:34:51,679 --> 00:34:53,159
Let our team of lawyers handle it.

259
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:56,080
I don't know how that video got leaked.

260
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:58,480
I'm looking into it, alright!

261
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:09,480
That video's very old.
We already paid them…

262
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:12,720
We took great care
of the girls in the video.

263
00:35:14,040 --> 00:35:15,880
I don't know why it still got posted.

264
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:24,840
I did everything I could.

265
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:30,040
I don't want people to associate
Cosmic Central with Techut.

266
00:35:50,080 --> 00:35:51,640
You did great.

267
00:35:52,920 --> 00:35:54,240
Keep going, okay?

268
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:14,680
Mr. Taiga, this is my father.

269
00:36:28,080 --> 00:36:29,880
Thank you for your work.

270
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:01,440
My father's a little taciturn,

271
00:37:01,520 --> 00:37:04,440
but I know that he really likes you.

272
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:25,440
The members of Fire Phoenix

273
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:31,000
will pay for every life
taken from Blazing Tiger.

274
00:38:51,040 --> 00:38:52,920
LEARN ABOUT FIRE PHOENIX
GLOBAL SECRET ORGANIZATION, MYTH OR FACT?

275
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:05,440
Send that designer guy
back to his country.

276
00:39:05,520 --> 00:39:08,520
Ever since that Taiga came,
our company's had so many problems.

277
00:39:10,080 --> 00:39:12,400
Horrible things happened
before he even came.

278
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:15,360
This happened because of Techut,
not Mr. Taiga!

279
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:19,920
Nunnapat! Since when
did you start going against me?

280
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:21,640
Then give me a reason.

281
00:39:21,720 --> 00:39:24,360
A good reason, not some nonsense,

282
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:25,720
and not from some jealous guy!

283
00:39:27,120 --> 00:39:29,840
Elites like you don't need love.

284
00:39:31,240 --> 00:39:33,320
Prioritize your own benefit.

285
00:39:33,400 --> 00:39:35,920
I'll find you a good husband,

286
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:38,400
not some weird designer like that guy.

287
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:47,040
Nun, don't talk back to your father.

288
00:39:47,120 --> 00:39:49,240
Wait till he calms down first.

289
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:50,800
Weird boyfriends…

290
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:53,480
They're perfect for you.

291
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:57,080
Techut!

292
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:01,720
- Damn you, Nun!
- Techut!

293
00:40:01,800 --> 00:40:04,400
Just leave. This isn't the time
for us to be fighting.

294
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:06,080
You're siblings, for God's sake.

295
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:08,840
Leave.

296
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:13,400
Weird boyfriend.

297
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:17,280
Why?

298
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:20,040
I did everything well,
but Dad never loves me.

299
00:40:20,120 --> 00:40:21,920
Techut's messed up countless times,

300
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:23,520
but Dad still loves him.

301
00:40:26,760 --> 00:40:28,480
Mr. Taiga treats me so well.

302
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:32,680
I love him, Mom. I love Mr. Taiga.

303
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:34,680
I understand, honey.

304
00:40:36,240 --> 00:40:38,320
Love is never wrong.

305
00:40:39,360 --> 00:40:42,240
Whoever you love, I'll love them too,

306
00:40:43,240 --> 00:40:44,880
but you need to be patient.

307
00:40:45,520 --> 00:40:50,000
We'll think of a way
for your dad to accept Mr. Taiga.

308
00:41:05,360 --> 00:41:06,520
<i>The websites she looked up…</i>

309
00:41:08,240 --> 00:41:11,480
LEARN ABOUT FIRE PHOENIX
GLOBAL SECRET ORGANIZATION, MYTH OR FACT?

310
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:13,840
…were about Fire Phoenix.

311
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:29,360
How many would you like today? Thank you.

312
00:41:32,080 --> 00:41:33,800
You're gonna be late to work today.

313
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:36,120
I'm not going. I got fired.

314
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:37,280
Really?

315
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:39,720
Can I have another?

316
00:41:42,080 --> 00:41:43,120
Don't hold back.

317
00:41:57,520 --> 00:41:59,920
You're still here, Mr. Designer?

318
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:02,480
Are you not done
saying goodbye to my sister?

319
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:07,720
Mr. Taiga will keep working here

320
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:09,400
until our Hi app gets launched.

321
00:42:09,480 --> 00:42:11,720
- That's not necessary.
- It is.

322
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:23,920
He is my personal designer, after all.

323
00:42:25,840 --> 00:42:28,840
I made a contract hiring him
to be my design consultant.

324
00:42:28,920 --> 00:42:30,840
Atinuch is getting his office ready.

325
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:34,800
Now Mr. Taiga can come in to work
whenever he wants.

326
00:42:53,080 --> 00:42:55,120
She cares more about a guy
than her own family!

327
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:57,600
She's defying me on purpose to annoy you.

328
00:42:57,680 --> 00:42:58,960
You know, yet you'll let her?

329
00:42:59,040 --> 00:43:00,520
Can't you see our stock here?

330
00:43:00,600 --> 00:43:04,160
I've got bigger responsibilities
than to fight over one person.

331
00:43:04,240 --> 00:43:07,920
But my gut tells me
that Taiga guy's bringing us trouble.

332
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:09,360
If you want to win,

333
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:12,000
you must deal with everything yourself.

334
00:43:12,640 --> 00:43:16,080
Prove to everyone
that Cosmic Central needs you.

335
00:43:20,760 --> 00:43:23,360
Hello, dear customers!

336
00:43:23,440 --> 00:43:25,480
Hello, hello!

337
00:43:25,560 --> 00:43:29,280
And our product for today
is fermented fish!

338
00:43:29,360 --> 00:43:31,280
‪Let me smell it.

339
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:36,120
The aroma's really strong!

340
00:43:36,200 --> 00:43:39,120
So fragrant and appetizing.
If you want to preorder it,

341
00:43:39,200 --> 00:43:42,600
do it now and you'll get this box

342
00:43:42,680 --> 00:43:44,720
with ten bottles of it, as well

343
00:43:44,800 --> 00:43:47,520
as ten grilled pork skewers for free!

344
00:44:01,360 --> 00:44:03,200
Thank you so much, Rin.

345
00:44:03,280 --> 00:44:06,200
Sales were crazy good today.

346
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:09,440
When the stuff gets delivered fast,
they preorder more.

347
00:44:17,680 --> 00:44:20,280
There's a light in all of us.

348
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:24,400
I wonder who said that.

349
00:44:29,280 --> 00:44:31,280
If you don't mind,

350
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:33,680
you can end your lease
and move in with me.

351
00:44:34,280 --> 00:44:36,720
You can move out once you find a new job.

352
00:44:36,800 --> 00:44:38,160
It'll help save money.

353
00:44:41,840 --> 00:44:43,600
I don't want to bother you, Aru.

354
00:44:43,680 --> 00:44:48,080
No, you won't! You said it
as if we've never helped each other.

355
00:44:48,760 --> 00:44:50,520
You've helped me before, Rin.

356
00:44:51,120 --> 00:44:52,720
Let me help you this time.

357
00:44:59,640 --> 00:45:00,480
Yeah?

358
00:45:08,400 --> 00:45:11,120
{\an8}You can leave once you finish this glass.

359
00:45:17,480 --> 00:45:19,080
{\an8}You're getting closer to our target.

360
00:45:20,400 --> 00:45:22,160
{\an8}<i>So you don't believe</i>

361
00:45:22,240 --> 00:45:24,920
{\an8}that Lirin, the youngest daughter
of Inspector Phumin, is dead?

362
00:46:02,440 --> 00:46:04,920
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

